-- 2010-10-07T14:06:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/ftse-100-benchmark-fluctuates-marks-spencer-gains-persimmon-declines.html
U.K. stocks retreated, as losses by
Kazakhmys Plc and Antofagasta Plc outweighed gains by Marks &
Spencer Group Plc and Burberry Group Plc.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index lost 0.3 percent to 5,664.08
at 3:05 p.m. in London, after earlier gaining as much as 0.5
percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
